    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-11 col-xl-10">
        <div class="d-flex align-items-end mb-5">
          <h3 class="m-0" id="miniinvasivebreast">Thinking about the minimal invasive</h3>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-11 col-xl-10">
        <div class="col-lg-5 mt-4 mt-lg-0" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100" style="width: 100% !important;">
          <div class="custom-accordion" id="accordion_miniinvasivebreast">

            <!-- Q1 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q1" 
                        aria-expanded="true" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q1">
                  What is a <span class="highlight">minimal-incision</span> breast reduction?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q1" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse show" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_1" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    <span class="highlight">Minimal-incision</span> breast reduction focuses on reducing breast size with <span class="bold">smaller scars</span> and less invasive techniques. Approaches like the <span class="highlight">lollipop incision</span> (around the areola and vertically down) or <span class="bold">liposuction-only</span> methods are common, aiming to minimize visible scarring while achieving a <span class="italic">natural, lifted breast shape</span>.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q2 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q2" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q2">
                  Who is a <span class="highlight">good candidate</span> for minimal-incision techniques?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q2" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_2" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    If you have <span class="bold">moderate breast size</span> and <span class="highlight">minimal sagging</span>, you might be a great candidate. <span class="italic">Liposuction-only</span> reductions work well if your breasts are composed mostly of fatty tissue without excess skin. But for <span class="bold">significant sagging</span> or larger reductions, traditional methods like the <span class="highlight">anchor incision</span> may be more suitable.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q3 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q3" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q3">
                  What are the <span class="highlight">benefits</span> of minimal-incision techniques?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q3" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_3" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    <span class="bold">Less scarring</span>: Smaller or hidden incisions (for instance, under the breast fold). <span class="italic">Faster recovery</span>: Reduced tissue trauma allows for quicker healing. <span class="highlight">Natural results</span>: Techniques such as the lollipop incision help create an aesthetically pleasing, lifted breast contour with minimal visible scars.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q4 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q4" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q4">
                  Are there <span class="highlight">limitations</span> to these techniques?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q4" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_4" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    Yes, they’re not ideal for everyone. For breasts with <span class="highlight">significant asymmetry</span>, <span class="bold">severe sagging</span>, or those needing large volume reduction, traditional methods may provide superior outcomes. Additionally, <span class="italic">liposuction-only</span> approaches do not address excess skin tightening or nipple repositioning.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q5 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q5" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q5">
                  How do I <span class="highlight">choose the right technique</span>?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q5" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_5" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    Your surgeon will assess your breast size, tissue composition (fat versus glandular), and overall goals during a detailed consultation. Open communication regarding scarring concerns and aesthetic expectations is key to determining whether a <span class="bold">minimal-incision</span> option or a traditional technique is suitable for you.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q6 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q6" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q6">
                  Can minimal-incision techniques deliver <span class="highlight">good results for larger reductions</span>?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q6" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_6" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    Techniques like the <span class="italic">lollipop incision</span> or liposuction-based methods are excellent for moderate reductions, especially in breasts with a high fat component. However, for <span class="bold">larger reductions</span> or cases involving significant sagging, the traditional anchor incision may be necessary to achieve optimal reshaping and lift.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q7 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q7" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q7">
                  What’s the deal with “<span class="highlight">scarless</span>” breast reduction?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q7" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_7" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    The term “<span class="highlight">scarless</span>” is somewhat misleading. Even with liposuction-based techniques, small scars (approximately 3-4mm) are inevitable but tend to be discreet and positioned within natural creases. This is suitable for <span class="italic">fatty breasts</span> lacking significant excess skin.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q8 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q8" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q8">
                  How does the <span class="highlight">lollipop incision</span> compare to the anchor technique?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q8" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_8" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    The <span class="highlight">lollipop incision</span>—around the areola and extending vertically—is less invasive than the anchor technique (which adds a horizontal scar along the breast crease). It offers quicker recovery and minimal scarring, ideal for moderate reductions, whereas the anchor incision is preferred for larger breasts or significant sagging to allow for comprehensive tissue reshaping.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q9 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q9" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q9">
                  What if I’m <span class="highlight">worried about scarring</span>?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q9" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_9" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    While some scarring is inevitable, proper aftercare—using silicone sheets, scar creams, and sun protection—can minimize its appearance. If scarring is a primary concern, options like liposuction-based or vertical incision techniques may be more appropriate. Discussing these concerns with your surgeon will help tailor the procedure to your needs.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Q10 -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link collapsed" 
                        type="button" 
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse" 
                        data-bs-target="#miniinvasivebreast_q10" 
                        aria-expanded="false" 
                        aria-controls="miniinvasivebreast_q10">
                  Can minimal-incision methods <span class="highlight">preserve nipple sensation and breastfeeding ability</span>?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="miniinvasivebreast_q10" 
                   class="accordion-collapse collapse" 
                   aria-labelledby="heading_miniinvasivebreast_10" 
                   data-bs-parent="#accordion_miniinvasivebreast">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="answer">
                    Yes, these advanced techniques strive to preserve the blood flow and nerve supply to the nipple–areola complex. While the lollipop and anchor methods generally maintain sensation and potential for breastfeeding, liposuction-only approaches do not reposition the nipple and might not address all aspects of functionality.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

          
